Package: colorblindr
Type: Package
Title: Simulate colorblindness in R figures
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c( 
    person("Claire D.", "McWhite", , "claire.mcwhite@utexas.edu", c("aut")),
    person("Claus O.", "Wilke", , "wilke@austin.utexas.edu", c("cre", "aut")))
Description: Provides a variety of functions that are helpful to simulate 
  the effects of colorblindness in R figures. Complete figures can be modified
  to simulate the effects of various types of colorblindness. The resulting 
  figures are standard grid objects and can be further manipulated or outputted
  as usual.
URL: https://github.com/clauswilke/colorblindr
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2),
    grDevices,
    colorspace (>= 99.0)
Imports:
    cowplot (> 0.8.0),
    dichromat,
    shiny (>= 1.0.0),
    methods
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
